## Key Nomenclature and Definitions

**Core Analytics Concepts:**
- **Events** - Discrete user actions or system occurrences with timestamp and property metadata
- **Properties** - Key-value attributes associated with events (event properties) or users (user properties)
- **Cohorts** - Dynamic user groups defined by behavioral criteria or demographic attributes
- **Segments** - Filtered subsets of users or events for targeted analysis and comparison
- **Sessions** - Temporally grouped user interactions with configurable timeout thresholds
- **Funnels** - Sequential event chains representing conversion processes with step-by-step analysis

**Experimentation Terminology:**
- **Flags** - Boolean or multi-variant feature toggles controlling functionality exposure
- **Variants** - Different implementations of features tested against control groups
- **Allocation** - Percentage-based user assignment to experimental conditions
- **Statistical Power** - Probability of detecting true effects in experimental results
- **Confidence Intervals** - Range estimates for experimental effect sizes

**Data Management Concepts:**
- **Device ID** - Persistent anonymous identifier for cross-session user tracking
- **User ID** - Customer-defined identifier for authenticated user experiences
- **Sample Rate** - Percentage of events or users included in data collection
- **Data Residency** - Geographic data storage location (US/EU server zones)
- **PII (Personally Identifiable Information)** - Sensitive data requiring special handling protocols

**Privacy and Compliance:**
- **Masking** - Automatic obfuscation of sensitive data elements in Session Replay
- **Consent Management** - User permission tracking for GDPR/CCPA compliance
- **Data Retention** - Configurable storage duration policies for different data types

